premise_source_doc_sentence: In 332 BCE the Macedonian Greeks under Alexander the Great conquered Israel , starting a long religious struggle that split the Jewish population into traditional  (  orthodox  )  and Hellenized components .

In the 330s BCE , Alexander the Great conquered the area now called Palestine , and the region changed hands numerous times during the wars of the Diadochi , ultimately joining the Seleucid Empire between 219 and 200 BCE .
Cyrus the Great respected the customs and religions of the lands he conquered .
Also registered as `` Seven Things I Hate About You '' , Cyrus developed the song during the Best of Both Worlds Tour while feeling numerous emotions for an ex-boyfriend , mainly anger .
Musically , `` 7 Things '' bears aspects of both country and pop rock , while the lyrics in the song 's refrain list seven traits Cyrus hates about an ex-boyfriend .
